Pre-Game Insights: Congo have not played a World Cup qualifier since their 4-2 defeat against Zambia in November.
Congo's second scheduled opponent, Eritrea, withdrew from the qualifiers.
Congo went an international friendly against Gabon in March, drawing 1-1.
Congo have lost their last four games across all competitions and have only won one of their last seven competitive matches since September 2022.
Congo have never won against Morocco in three meetings, losing twice and drawing once.
Morocco secured a 2-1 victory over Zambia in a World Cup qualifier recently, taking an early lead through a Hakim Ziyech penalty and doubling their advantage via Eliesse Ben Seghir.
Morocco are currently top of Group E with six points from two games, three clear of the next three teams behind them.
Congo opted for a relatively inexperienced group, with 12 players earning their first-ever senior call-up.
Morocco are rich with options in their squad, with the trio of Ziyech, Seghir and Brahim Diaz offering support to Youssef En-Neysri who spearheads the attack.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match venue was changed from Kinshasa to Morocco's Grand Stadium of Agadir due to FIFA not approving the original venue.
Congo's upcoming game against Morocco has been relocated to Morocco's Grand Stadium of Agadir.
The Central Africans have a poor record against Morocco, having never won in three meetings.
